article.headline: Morgan St. 69, North Carolina A&T 60
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Jamar Smith scored 20 points and grabbed eight rebounds and Ronald Timus scored 16 of his 19 points in the second half as Morgan State defeated North Carolina A&T, 69-60, Monday night. Joseph McLean scored 20 points, Reggie Holmes scored eight points and had three steals and Timothy Berkley had 10 rebounds for Morgan. After opening the season 0-6, Morgan (6-11, 4-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) has won two straight and four of its last six games. Jason Wills scored 20 points and grabbed a game-high 11 rebounds for North Carolina A&T (6-11, 4-3). Walter Booth had nine points and four rebounds and Trahern Chaplin had six points and six rebounds for the Aggies. Trailing 36-29 two minutes into the second half, Morgan rallied back with an 18-2 run and led 47-38 with 13:01 remaining. North Carolina A&T eventually pulled to within 49-47. But, the Aggies would not get any closer as the Bears outscored them 20-13 over the final 9:41. North Carolina A&T closed the first half with an offensive spurt as the Aggies scored seven straight points and led 31-25 late in the opening 20-minutes. Morgan responded with baskets by McLean and Smith to pull within 31-29 at halftime.
